      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): add Authorization header to provider preflight probe",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCron job preflight check (`GET {baseUrl}/models`) was missing auth or using wrong auth for local provider probes. Also fixed credential resolution path, error redaction, and CI compilation errors.\n\n## Changes\n\n### P0: Error Redaction — Prevent auth secret leakage\n- **`model-preflight.runtime.ts`**: Replaced `String(params.error)` with `formatErrorMessage()` — the shared redacting formatter that masks Bearer tokens, API keys, and other credentials before they appear in cron preflight logs or delivery payloads.\n\n### P0.5: AgentDir/WorkspaceDir Type Contract — Fix TS compilation\n- **`model-preflight.runtime.ts`**: Added `agentDir?: string; workspaceDir?: string;` to `preflightCronModelProvider`'s parameter type\n- **`run.ts`**: Passes actual `agentDir` and `workspaceDir` values from `PreparedCronRunContext` into preflight call\n- **Fixes 3 CI failures** (checks-node-compact-small-3, check-prod-types, check-test-types) — all failing with TS2339 on these missing props\n\n### P1: Support `request.auth.mode: \"header\"` — Custom header auth\n- Extended auth extraction to handle `header` mode (custom header name/value/prefix), not just `authorization-bearer`\n- `probeLocalProviderEndpoint` now accepts `extraHeaders: Record<string, string>` for custom auth headers\n- Falls through to `resolveApiKeyForProvider` for Bearer auth when custom header is present — both headers can coexist\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Cron job preflight GET /models to local provider was sending no Authorization header (original bug), and after the initial attempt lacked full credential chain resolution, had no custom-header auth support, leaked auth secrets in error logs, and failed TS compilation.\n\n**Real environment tested:**\n- **OS:** Ubuntu 24.04 (Oracle VPS)\n- **Runtime:** Node.js v24.15.0\n- **OpenClaw version:** 2026.5.18 (npm install)\n- **Provider:** LiteLLM proxy at http://127.0.0.1:4000\n- **Auth method:** LITELLM_API_KEY environment variable\n\n**Evidence after fix:** LiteLLM proxy logs before (top) and after (bottom) the patch show GET /models now gets 200 OK instead of 401:\n\n![Before/after terminal comparison](https://github.com/samson1357924/openclaw/releases/download/evd-pr83648/evidence-pr-img.jpg)\n\nBefore — no auth header, cron preflight triggers 401:\n```text\n17:30:05 LiteLLM Proxy:ERROR - Exception occured - No api key passed in.\nRequester IP Address:127.0.0.1\n127.0.0.1:58244 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 401 Unauthorized\n127.0.0.1:50768 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n```\n\nAfter — auth header sent, preflight succeeds:\n```text\n127.0.0.1:45914 - \"GET /models HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n127.0.0.1:49934 - \"POST /chat/completions HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** GET /models response changed from 401 Unauthorized to 200 OK. No more \"No api key passed in\" errors. Cron preflight cache populates correctly. All existing tests pass (21 tests, 0 failures).\n\n**Verification:**\n- ✅ 21 tests pass (13 original + 8 new for header-mode auth)\n- ✅ 3 CI compilation errors fixed (TS2339 on agentDir/workspaceDir)\n- ✅ Code reviewer: APPROVE (zero critical issues)\n- ✅ Security: Auth secrets redacted in error messages via shared redacting formatter\n- ✅ Feature: Both `authorization-bearer` and `header` auth modes supported\n\n## Files Changed\n\n- `src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.ts` — auth resolution, error redaction, header-mode support\n- `src/cron/isolated-agent/run.ts` — wire agentDir/workspaceDir to preflight\n- `src/cron/isolated-agent/model-preflight.runtime.test.ts` — 21 tests (13 original + 8 new)\n\nCloses #83648\n",
        "branch": "fix/cron-preflight-clean",
